# 1Password secret references for the AI image skills.
#
# These are *references*, not secrets — safe to commit. The real values stay in
# your 1Password vault and are injected at runtime by `op run --env-file=...`.
#
# Recommended (least privilege, per 1Password best practices):
#   - Keep these API keys in a DEDICATED vault (e.g. "AI") that holds nothing
#     else, so a leaked/abused read is limited to just these keys.
#   - For interactive local use, authenticate with the 1Password app integration
#     (biometric unlock) — no service-account token written to disk.
#     https://developer.1password.com/docs/cli/about-biometric-unlock/
#   - Service accounts are for unattended automation; if you use one, scope it to
#     the AI vault only and never store its token in plaintext.
#
# Setup:
#   1. cp .claude/ai.env.example .claude/ai.env   # ai.env is gitignored
#   2. Edit the op:// paths below to match your vault / item / field.
#      Find the exact reference with:  op item get "Gemini API" --format json
#      or copy it from the 1Password app: item → field → "Copy Secret Reference".
#   3. Sign in once per session: `op signin` (or enable the 1Password desktop app
#      CLI integration for biometric unlock).
#
# Format: op://<vault>/<item>/<field>

GEMINI_API_KEY="op://Private/Gemini API/credential"
OPENROUTER_API_KEY="op://Private/OpenRouter/credential"
